full_text:
Bob Wilson's key rules: 
1. Find intelligent brokers
2. What 2-3 influences will make stock move? 
3. Watch how stock responds
4. Seek uncommon insight
5. Look forward to pleasant surprises
6. Kick a dog when it's down (short)
7. Wait for move to start before entering
name: Michael Fritzell (Asian Century Stocks)

full_text:
8. Never fall in love with a company
9. Focus on the big picture not the details
10. Sell a stock is elaborate research reports appear
11. Sell popular stocks quickly if news turn bad
12. Better to sell a winning stock too late than too early
name: Michael Fritzell (Asian Century Stocks)

full_text:
13. Management cannot turn around a poor business
14. Don't accept management comments at face value
15. One-time gains from positive news won't persist
16. In bad times, collect clues for good times
17. Ignore institutional ownership
18. Pay attention to managerial motivation
name: Michael Fritzell (Asian Century Stocks)
